    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-09-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-09-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="1390"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1390">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 412.11/136.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of War</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">War Department</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 25, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of a
                    letter of the 18th instant from the Acting Secretary of State, replying to one
                    from this Department of the 3d instant, in which is inclosed a list of the
                    claims on file in the Department of State arising in the United States but
                    growing out of the revolution in adjacent Mexican territory.</p>
                <p>The commission of Army officers appointed under the joint resolution of Congress
                    is ready to begin its investigation of the claims, but most of them are not yet
                    filed. It will facilitate the beginning of work if your Department would
                    transmit to the War Department the original petitions or memorials on file in
                    your office, provided, of course, that such action is entirely consistent with
                    the purposes of the Department of State in respect to the claims in
                    question.</p>
                <p>Very respectfully,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Shaw Oliver.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
